The paper discusses the use of machine learning in game content generation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on explainability and interaction with human designers suggests a strong emphasis on machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of design patterns as a vocabulary and mode of interaction also suggests a connection to graphics (cs.GR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
